Dedeman Madencilik, a Turkish
mining company, has found chrome reserves with an estimated
value of $3 billion at its Aladag facility near the city of
Adana,  Hurriyet  reported, citing Yunus Soysal, a company
engineer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
